SubItem.Name: SubIndex 000
SubItem.Comment: This object contains parameters to manage the automatic motor brake control.

SubItem.Name: Motor brake type
SubItem.Comment: Activates drive internal automatic brake control.

SubItem.Name: Motor brake usage
SubItem.Comment: Configures the error reaction behavior of the motor brake.

SubItem.Name: Drive on delay time
SubItem.Comment: With the transition of the PDS state machine to "operation enabled" "drive on delay time" is started. The drive follows the command values after the "drive on delay time" has elapsed. The motor brake management uses this time to unlock the motor brake before motion is enabled.

SubItem.Name: Drive off delay time
SubItem.Comment: After "operation enabled" of the PDS state machine is removed and the axis is in the standstill window, the locking of the brake is initiated and the drive off delay time is started. The torque/force remains activated in the drive until the configured drive off delay time is elapsed. The motor brake management uses this time to lock the motor brake before the torque/force is switched off..

SubItem.Name: Motor brake current monitoring level
SubItem.Comment: If the motor brake current remains below the specified threshold, an error is reported. Motor brake current monitoring level is only active if brake control is enabled.

SubItem.Name: SubIndex 000
SubItem.Comment: This object contains parameters to configure the connected motor.

SubItem.Name: Configured motor type
SubItem.Comment: This object indicates the configured motor type.

SubItem.Name: Pole pairs
SubItem.Comment: This object indicates the motor pole pairs.

SubItem.Name: Motor peak current
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor peak current. If the electronic datasheet of the motor is available take "Peak current".

SubItem.Name: Motor nominal voltage
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor nominal voltage. If the electronic datasheet is available take "Nominal voltage" according to the selected mains voltage.

SubItem.Name: Motor max voltage
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor max voltage. If the electronic datasheet is available take "Max voltage".

SubItem.Name: Winding resistance R
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the winding resistance R (phase to phase 20C). If the electronic datasheet is available take "Winding resistance Ph-Ph 20C".

SubItem.Name: Winding inductance Ld
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the direct axis winding inductance Ld (phase to phase). If the electronic datasheet is available take "Ld Ph-Ph".

SubItem.Name: Winding inductance Lq
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the direct winding inductance Lq. If the electronic datasheet is available take "Lq Ph-Ph".

SubItem.Name: Motor warning temperature
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor temperature warning threshold. If the electronic datasheet is available take "T motor warn limit".

SubItem.Name: Motor shut down temperature
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor temperature error threshold. If the electronic datasheet is available take "T motor err limit".

SubItem.Name: Motor moment of inertia
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the inertia of rotor including brake and encoder. If the electronic datasheet is available take "J motor with brake".

SubItem.Name: Motor rated speed
SubItem.Comment: This object indicates the motor calculated speed. Its calculated from the motor parameters.

SubItem.Name: Motor rated torque
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor rated torque at rated speed. If the electronic datasheet is available take "Rated torque" according to the selected mains voltage.

SubItem.Name: Commutation offset
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor commutation offset. Beckhoff motors use the default value (0).

SubItem.Name: Motor temperature sensor type
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the motor temperature sensor type.

SubItem.Name: SubIndex 000
SubItem.Comment: This object contains actual values from the module SyncServoMotor.

SubItem.Name: Actual motor I2T current limit
SubItem.Comment: This object is to monitor the thermal motor I^{2}T model current limitation. If the estimated I^{2}T value exceeds the threshold value the current will be limited to motor I_{0} (0x6075).

SubItem.Name: Thermal motor utilization
SubItem.Comment: This object is to indicate the actual motor utilization.

SubItem.Name: Estimated motor copper losses
SubItem.Comment: Internal value for estimated motor copper losses.

SubItem.Name: Estimated motor iron losses
SubItem.Comment: Internal value for estimated motor iron losses.

SubItem.Name: Motor I2T active
SubItem.Comment: This internal state indicates a current reduction due to the thermal motor model.

SubItem.Name: Actual motor temperature
SubItem.Comment: This object provides the measured motor winding temperature. It is usually acquired via the motor internal KTY.

SubItem.Name: SubIndex 000
SubItem.Comment: This object contains parameters to configure the Motor commutation monitoring

SubItem.Name: Speed threshold
SubItem.Comment: The minimum speed for detecting a commutation error is 'Max motor speed' (0x6080) multiplied by 'Speed threshold'

SubItem.Name: Voltage threshold
SubItem.Comment: The BEMF level for detecting a commutation error is 'Motor nominal voltage' (0x42C0:03) multiplied by 'Voltage threshold'

SubItem.Name: SubIndex 000
SubItem.Comment: These objects configure the motor thermal model.

SubItem.Name: Motor thermal time constant
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the time constant for the whole motor. If an electronic datasheet is available take "Motor thermal constant" and scale it to seconds.

SubItem.Name: Winding thermal time constant
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the time constant of the copper winding only. If an electronic datasheet is available take "Time constant i^{2}T".

SubItem.Name: Warning limit
SubItem.Comment: This object shall configure the thermal motor utilization warning limit.

SubItem.Name: Error limit
SubItem.Comment: This object shall configure the thermal motor utilization error limit.

SubItem.Name: Reaction
SubItem.Comment: This object configures the reaction in case reaching the thermal motor utilization error limit.

SubItem.Name: Partial fraction factor
SubItem.Comment: This object describes the thermal resistor fraction factor of the motor.

Object.Name: [SG] Motor parameters
Object.Comment: This object contains parameters to configure the connected motor.

Object.Name: [SG] SyncServoMotor actual values
Object.Comment: This object contains actual values from the module SyncServoMotor.

Object.Name: [SG] Motor torque characteristic
Object.Comment: This object describes the motor torque characteristic of a cold (40C) motor. The torque as a function of current curve is approximated by a third order polynomial. Three pairs of values are required. Standstill current and torque, peak current and torque and a pair of values between standstill and peak. The values can be read from the motor electronic datasheet (XEDS file).

Object.Name: [SG] Motor commutation monitoring parameters
Object.Comment: This object contains parameters to configure the Motor commutation monitoring

Object.Name: [SG] Motor temperature sensor characteristic
Object.Comment: This object describes the R(T) curve of the motor winding temperature sensor.

Object.Name: [SG] Motor thermal model
Object.Comment: These objects configure the motor thermal model.

Object.Name: [SG] Motor standstill current
Object.Comment: This object indicates the motor standstill current (I_{0}). If an electronic datasheet is available "Standstill current" will be read and scaled to mA.

Object.Name: [SG] Motor standstill torque
Object.Comment: This object indicates the motor standstill torque (M_{0})/force (F_{c}). If an electronic datasheet of the motor is available "Standstill current" (I_{0}) will be multiplied by the torque constant (K_{t})/(K_{f}). The value is scaled to mNm/mN.

Object.Name: [SG] Max motor speed
Object.Comment: This object shall indicate the configured maximal allowed speed for the motor in either direction. It is used to protect the motor and is taken from the motor data sheet.
